@*
    Client-side jQuery unobtrusive validation is intentionally disabled.

    These forms (Login/Register/ResetPassword/ChangePassword) are fully validated
    server-side via ModelState — they post and re-render with field errors, so they
    are functionally correct without any JavaScript.

    The previous markup referenced ~/lib/jquery-validation/* which is not vendored
    (404 + MIME errors), and the CDN fallback can't load because the site CSP is
    script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' (no external origins). jQuery itself is also
    not loaded anywhere on the site. Re-enabling client-side validation would mean
    vendoring jquery + jquery-validation + jquery-validation-unobtrusive locally
    under wwwroot/lib so they satisfy the 'self' CSP. Tracked as a follow-up.
*@
